        </figure>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6047e4c6dfc6544ed63c758e/1633678304339-7W04TVHZUVIDTR6B8OLN/unsplash-image-dbpLrMALyiM.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1127"><media:title type="plain">How to Destroy Paper Documents without a Shredder: 6 Effective Alternatives</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>What Documents Should You Keep &amp; What Should You Shred?</title><dc:creator>Guest User</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 13 Jun 2025 01:00:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.merlinshredding.com/blog/what-documents-to-keep-versus-shred-w4m9g</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6047e4c6dfc6544ed63c758e:6047f052f7b2925db6ce25fd:62fd8f147a6bbb27e3c58117</guid><description><![CDATA[A common question to ask is, how do I know what needs to be properly 
destroyed, and what should I make sure I keep for a certain length of time? 
