        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Think about your own personal devices. It is fairly uncommon to share your device with your household members nowadays, as we each value our own privacy and maintenance of the device. If you were to lend your laptop to a family member, you would trust that they would not download illegitimate softwares or visit high-risk websites. </p><p class="">Now, put it in this perspective: your employer is lending you their computer for an extended period of time. Putting the device at risk could run some serious consequences, as business networks are likely to be a target for scams and hackers.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
