        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Paper contributes to 6 million tons or ⅓ of Canada's waste in landfills and it takes 234 liters of water to produce only 1 kg of paper, all the while only ¼ of paper is being recycled. Despite paper being the better alternative to plastic, if not properly recycled, it can still leave a huge impact on our planet. Between business, schools and just leisure use, if everyone committed to the small act of recycling their paper waste, not only would it be good for the planet, it could help further protect your data.&nbsp;</p><p class=""><br><br></p><h3>How shredding can help</h3><p class="">Shredding is one of the best and easiest ways to recycle paper, as most shredding companies have opted for recycling to be their means of disposal. This has become a popular trend among shredding companies not only due to the environment aspect but in repurposing those shredded bits, it further destroys any information stashed in those pieces. By shredding and recycling just 1 ton of your paper waste/old documents you could be saving approximately 17 fully grown trees, 7000 gallons of water, 680 gallons of oil and 4,100 kilowatt hours of electricity. And it really is as easy as shredding your paper with a company like Merlin Shredding. We can come to you and help you make sure your paper is shredded and properly disposed of.&nbsp;</p><p class=""><br><br></p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
