  <p class="">These days we all rely on fast and convenient online shopping more than ever before. So what does this mean for our online safety? According to <a href="https://www150.statcan.gc.ca/n1/daily-quotidien/201020/dq201020a-eng.htm"><span>Stats Canada</span></a>, in 2019 one-fifth of the Canadian business population was impacted by a cyber security incident. While you shouldn’t quit online shopping, it is important you are protecting your private information.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Make sure to check out our other tips about<a href="https://www.merlinshredding.com/blog/working-from-home-2021-how-are-you-keeping-your-business-documents-safe"><span> keeping digital business documents safe</span></a> and keep reading for three tips to keep you safe when shopping online!</p><blockquote><p class=""><a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/taxes.html"> </a></p></blockquote><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><h2>Create strong passwords.</h2></li></ol><p class="">It is often convenient to make an account on your favourite shopping sites. Since these accounts store your personal information, you want to create the strongest password possible. Make sure it is long, switches between upper and lower case letters, uses numbers and symbols, is a made up word or phrase and has no personal information. It is also important to change your passwords regularly and avoid repeating them across multiple sites. If that seems overwhelming, try a <a href="https://nordpass.com/?gclid=Cj0KCQjw7pKFBhDUARIsAFUoMDYoHPPVjfpdUOSjm3QhqTZ9CoflxsUBFrAmSn--aJ7lzLqsShtH98MaAn9WEALw_wcB"><span>Password Manager</span></a>! .</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
