  <p class="">When scrolling through your favourite social media site, you might get a targeted advertisement. While it can be tempting to click on the amazing deal, it is not recommended. Instead, go directly to the website and make sure the offer is real. Doing this quick step will keep you safe and still get great sales!</p><blockquote><p class="">Using these tips means you can shop online and not be worried about your privacy! Don’t forget to make sure you are still shredding any physical documents you received with your orders! Receipts, mail, and shipping labels can all contain private information that should be shredded! We’re always happy to help so feel free to connect with us at  <a href="mailto:info@merlinshredding.com"><span>info@merlinshredding.com</span></a>.</p></blockquote>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6047e4c6dfc6544ed63c758e/1621615865478-9ZRSHSDAJJRWAPKNF6E6/cyber-security-privacy-shredding-alberta-edmonton.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1000"><media:title type="plain">3 Easy Ways to Make Sure You are Safe When Online Shopping</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Top 4 Cyber Threats to Businesses in 2022</title><dc:creator>Guest User</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 30 May 2022 19:33:41 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.merlinshredding.com/blog/top-4-cyber-threats-to-businesses-in-2022</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6047e4c6dfc6544ed63c758e:6047f052f7b2925db6ce25fd:62951803408ae823285c28c8</guid><description><![CDATA[A recent report including data from 1,400 Chief Information Security 
