  <p class="">This year, 1,400 CISOs (Chief Information Security Officers) were interviewed across 14 countries to discover what the top threats are as it relates to cyber security for businesses in 2022.</p><p class="">The report speaks to the change in landscape and precautions to consider as more employees are working remotely, leading to an increased risk of cyberattacks. </p><p class="">So what are the top cyber threats posed to businesses in 2022?</p><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>Insider Threats</strong> - This continues to be of highest importance to consider for all organizations. The CISO report also includes ways to mitigate inside, employee threats in their own strategic plans.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Email fraud</strong> - Employees are continuing to be at risk for phishing emails and other threats that allow cyber attackers to access company data.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>DDoS attacks (Distributed Denial of Service)</strong> - These specific type of attacks have increased the most over the past few years, making them one of the highest threats across the globe in cyber security.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Compromising Cloud accounts</strong> - Without enough protection, cloud accounts continue to grow as an easy point of entry for cyber attacks on organizations. </p></li></ol><p class="">All of the cyber security threats emphasize importance of thorough destruction of hardware as well as physical documentation through secure, professional shredding. </p><p class="">To see the full report and read more CISO recommendations, <a href="https://www.proofpoint.com/us/resources/white-papers/voice-of-the-ciso-report"><strong>click here.</strong> </a></p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/6047e4c6dfc6544ed63c758e/1653939244352-RXU61UV1O78A4BEJ2K9T/photo_group-of-employees-working-on-project.png?format=1500w